HEBREW: נַפְתָּלִ֗י לֹֽא־הוֹרִ֞ישׁ אֶת־יֹשְׁבֵ֤י בֵֽית־שֶׁ֙מֶשׁ֙ וְאֶת־יֹשְׁבֵ֣י בֵית־עֲנָ֔ת וַיֵּ֕שֶׁב בְּקֶ֥רֶב הַֽכְּנַעֲנִ֖י יֹשְׁבֵ֣י הָאָ֑רֶץ וְיֹשְׁבֵ֤י בֵֽית־שֶׁ֙מֶשׁ֙ וּבֵ֣ית עֲנָ֔ת הָי֥וּ לָהֶ֖ם לָמַֽס׃ (ס)
ENGLISH: Neither did Naftali drive out the inhabitants of Bet-shemesh, nor the inhabitants of Bet-῾anat; but he dwelt among the Kena῾ani, the inhabitants of the land: nevertheless the inhabitants of Bet-shemesh and of Bet-῾anat became tributaries to them.
